        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3706602212" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13942470986254503410">I can&apos;t believe that almost 85 years ago what Ambedkar wrote in this book is still absolutely relevant to the Caste/Varna system in Hinduism. Ambedkar said that Religion should be based on principles, not based on some rules without any reasoning. If Gandhi is true to his conscience that all the caste discrimination in Vedas, Masnusmiriti and shastras are interpolation then he should have honestly agreed to Ambedkar&apos;s idea of abandoning all of them and create one holy book based on principles wi</span>
  <span id="freeText13942470986254503410" style="display:none">I can't believe that almost 85 years ago what Ambedkar wrote in this book is still absolutely relevant to the Caste/Varna system in Hinduism. Ambedkar said that Religion should be based on principles, not based on some rules without any reasoning. If Gandhi is true to his conscience that all the caste discrimination in Vedas, Masnusmiriti and shastras are interpolation then he should have honestly agreed to Ambedkar's idea of abandoning all of them and create one holy book based on principles without such caste/varna discrimination. It would have actually made Hinduism one of the greatest religions. Ambedkar clearly exposed Gandhi's double standards. I can't believe our educational system made us read Gandhi's Truth of Experiments, but not even a fraction of Ambedkar's writings. Ambedkar should be inarguably recognized as one of the founding fathers of the country.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13942470986254503410" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
