<div id="review_3195849070" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3195849070" />
    <a title="Bhavesh Mehta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5055213-bhavesh-mehta"><img alt="Bhavesh Mehta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518089275p2/5055213.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3195849070?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bhavesh Mehta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bhavesh Mehta" href="/user/show/5055213-bhavesh-mehta">Bhavesh Mehta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5055213-bhavesh-mehta?shelf=indian-author">indian-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5055213-bhavesh-mehta?shelf=indian-history">indian-history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3195849070" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2212605792909133928">It was painful reading Annihilation of Caste being a Brahmin, but I am glad I did. I have heard arguments in favor of caste system from the members of my community where they sometimes proclaimed it to be a divine proclamation and sometimes a necessity to maintain social order. <br/><br/>Ambedkar with his rational facts refutes each argument without being overly pretentious. He counter the Indian distressing scenario taking help from European examples. I also in a gloomy way enjoyed the narration style th</span>
  <span id="freeText2212605792909133928" style="display:none">It was painful reading Annihilation of Caste being a Brahmin, but I am glad I did. I have heard arguments in favor of caste system from the members of my community where they sometimes proclaimed it to be a divine proclamation and sometimes a necessity to maintain social order. <br /><br />Ambedkar with his rational facts refutes each argument without being overly pretentious. He counter the Indian distressing scenario taking help from European examples. I also in a gloomy way enjoyed the narration style that keeps you engaged with the text that talks about an extremely serious matter.<br /><br />The only minute objection that I have with his speech is related to his disgust for Hinduism. Perhaps, if he had been a bit lenient on the religion and had also expressed his feelings about Buddhism then maybe this work could have presented to us the complete ideology of Ambedkar. Nevertheless, it is a very important book for anyone who wants to understand how caste system cripples Hinduism and why it is important to fight it even in the 21st century for achieving the goal of equality. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2212605792909133928" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


